{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> τῑμωρ-ία</b>, <br /> Ionic -ίη, ἡ, <b>retribution, vengeance</b> (differing from κόλασις, corrective punishment, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Rhetorica” 1369b12), ἐς τ... παρασκευαζομένοισι 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 5.90; τ. καὶ τίσις [prev. author] 7.8.ά, cf. NT.Heb.10.29, etc.\">NT+5th c.BC+</a>]; πατρὸς τ. <b>vengeance taken for</b> him, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Orestes” 425 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; μητρὸς αἵματος τιμωρίαι <b>for having shed</b> a mother's blood, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work] 400 \">Refs</a>]; ἐπὶ τῇ ἡμετέρᾳ τ. for the purpose of <b>punishing</b> us, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 3.63; Λεωνίδην ἐάν τις ἀποκτείνῃ.. τὴν τ. εἶναι καθάπερ ἐάν τις Ἀθηναίων ἀποθάνῃ “IG” 12.56.16, compare 154.12; οὐκ ἔχει τιμωρίαν γὰρ τἀδίκημ᾽, ἔγκλημα δέ 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus “Περικειρομένη” 253 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἡ κατὰ τῶν προδιδόντων τ. <b>vengeance</b> against or upon.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Lycurgus Orator 140, compare 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 18.274, 4th-3rd c.BC: Dinarchus Orator 1.105; τ. ἐσομένη ἔς τινα 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.123, compare 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 22.55; τ. ὑπὲρ τοῦ ἀδικηθέντος 5th c.BC: Antipho Orator 6.6, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 20.19: with Verbs, of the avenger, ποιεῖσθαι τιμωρίαν\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] execute <b>vengeance</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 21.26, etc.\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; τινος on one, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Andocides Orator 4.18; τ. ὑπὲρ ὧν ἐπεπόνθειν λαβεῖν 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 24.8 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; but παρά τινος λαμβάνειν τ. exact <b>it</b> from him, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Philemo Comicus 88.14 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; of the wrongdoer, τ. Ἀθηνῶν ηὗρε found, i.e. suffered, <b>vengeance</b> at Athens' hand, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Persae” 473 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; τιμωρίας τυγχάνειν <b>to be punished</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Gorgias” 472d, “PEnteux.” 50.7 (3rd c.BC)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>], etc. (but also, obtain <b>vengeance</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.74, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 4.6.7); τ. ἀντιδοῦναι 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.53; τίνειν 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 905a, etc.; ὑπέχειν 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 6.80, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 716b, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of persons in authority, αἱ τ. εἰσὶ παρὰ τῶν θεῶν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.120 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τ. δοῦναί τινι give him <b>right of vengeance</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 23.7, compare [prev. work]54, 59.86; so τὰς τ. τοῖς ἰδιώταις ἐποίησε βραδείας [prev. author] 26.4 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]: <i>plural</i>, <b>penalties</b>, λαμβάνειν τὰς ἀξίας τ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Antiphanes Comicus 247 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; ταῖς ἐσχάταις τιμωρεῖσθαι τ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 579a, compare “Lg.” 943d, +others\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of state-punishments, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.2Mac.6.26, +others\">LXX</a>]; οἱ ἐπὶ τῶν τ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Artoxerxes” 14, 17 \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]; of divine punishments, ἐξορκίζω σε.. κατὰ &lt;τῶν ἐπὶ&gt; τῶν τ. τεταγμένων [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “PMag.Lond.” 121.303. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>succour</b>, εὑρήσεται τ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.148 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἡ ἀφ᾽ ὑμῶν τ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.69, compare 5.112; τ. ποιεῖσθαί τινι [prev. author] 1.124 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τ. τοῦ τεθνεῶτος <b>due</b> to him, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Antipho Orator 1.5. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> of <b>medical and</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ διαίτης ὀξέων” 18 (_plural_); compare τιμωρέω 11.2. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G5098","accentedUnicode":"τιμωρία","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G5097","matchingForm":"τιμωρέω","stepTransliteration":"timōreō","gloss":"to punish","_zh_tw_Gloss":"用刑, 受刑","_es_Gloss":"castigar","_zh_Gloss":"用刑, 受刑"}],"shortDef":"punishment","mediumDef":"<b>punishment,</b> <ref='Heb.10.29'>Heb. 10:29</ref>*","stepGloss":"punishment","stepTransliteration":"timōria","count":1,"_es_Definition":"castigo, sanción","_zh_tw_Definition":"懲罰 (來10:29)","_zh_Definition":"惩罚 (来10:29)","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"sự trừng phạt; sự trừng trị","_zh_tw_Gloss":"刑罰!","_es_Gloss":"castigo","_zh_Gloss":"刑罚!"}]}